snippet: A 42-year-old man accused of being high while operating demolition equipment when a building collapsed and killed six people will be charged with involuntary manslaughter.
abstract: Philadelphia city officials says Sean Benschop, who is accused of being high while operating demolition equipment when building collapsed and killed six people, will be charged with involuntary manslaughter.
lead_paragraph: A 42-year-old man accused of being high while operating demolition equipment when a building collapsed and killed six people will be charged with involuntary manslaughter.

headline.main: Pennsylvania: Worker Sought in Demolition Deaths
